.TH "WebGL2RenderingContext.clearBuffer" "JS" "September 28, 2024" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
WebGL2RenderingContext.clearBuffer \- WebGL2RenderingContext:
clearBufferfiuv method
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]WebGL2RenderingContext.clearBuffer[fiuv]()\f[B]\f[R]
methods of the WebGL 2 API clear buffers from the currently bound
framebuffer.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
clearBufferfv(buffer, drawbuffer, values)
clearBufferfv(buffer, drawbuffer, values, srcOffset)

clearBufferiv(buffer, drawbuffer, values)
clearBufferiv(buffer, drawbuffer, values, srcOffset)

clearBufferuiv(buffer, drawbuffer, values)
clearBufferuiv(buffer, drawbuffer, values, srcOffset)

clearBufferfi(buffer, drawbuffer, depth, stencil)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]buffer\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLenum\f[R] specifying the buffer to clear.
Possible values are:
.RS
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]gl.COLOR\f[R]: Color buffer.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]gl.DEPTH\f[R]: Depth buffer.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]gl.STENCIL\f[R]: Stencil buffer.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]gl.DEPTH_STENCIL\f[R]: clears depth and stencil buffers (used with
\f[CR]clearBufferfi\f[R]).
.RE
.TP
\f[B]drawBuffer\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLint\f[R] specifying the draw buffer to clear.
.TP
\f[B]values\f[R]
An \f[CR]Array\f[R] of \f[CR]GLint\f[R], \f[CR]GLuint\f[R] or
\f[CR]GLfloat\f[R] values or an \f[CR]Int32Array\f[R],
\f[CR]Uint32Array\f[R] or \f[CR]Float32Array\f[R] specifying the values
to clear to.
.TP
\f[B]depth\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLfloat\f[R] specifying the value to clear a depth render buffer
to.
.TP
\f[B]stencil\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLint\f[R] specifying the value to clear the stencil render
buffer to.
.SS Return value
None (\f[CR]undefined\f[R]).
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
gl.clearBufferiv(gl.COLOR, 0, \f[B]new\f[R] Int32Array([r, g, b, a]));
gl.clearBufferuiv(gl.COLOR, 0, \f[B]new\f[R] Uint32Array([r, g, b, a]));
gl.clearBufferfv(gl.COLOR, 0, \f[B]new\f[R] Float32Array([r, g, b, a]));
gl.clearBufferfv(gl.COLOR, 0, [0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0]);
gl.clearBufferfi(gl.DEPTH_STENCIL, 0, 1.0, 0);
.EE
